    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A War Over Rent, on Two Coasts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas J Charters letter says Paul Krugman's June 7 Op-Ed column shows folly of rent control laws in New York and San Francisco</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''A Rent Affair'' (column, June 7), Paul Krugman offers an excellent analysis of your June 6 news article about the plight of renters in San Francisco. The excesses of the rental market and their causes are no different in San Francisco than they are closer to home. Substitute ''New York'' for ''San Francisco,'' and the article reads just as accurately.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''A Rent Affair'' (column, June 7), Paul Krugman offers an excellent analysis of your June 6 news article about the plight of renters in San Francisco. The excesses of the rental market and their causes are no different in San Francisco than they are closer to home. Substitute ''New York'' for ''San Francisco,'' and the article reads just as accurately.</p>
        <p>New Yorkers, like San Franciscans, ''literally don't want to know'' about the twisted logic of rent control.</p>
        <p>THOMAS J. CHARTERS  New York, June 7, 2000</p>
      </block>
